        <!-- F√ìRMULAS HIDR√ÅULICAS -->
        <section id="formulas-hidraulica" class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-tint"></i> 5. F√ìRMULAS HIDR√ÅULICAS COMPLETAS</h2>
            
            <div class="subsection">
                <h3 class="subsection-title"><i class="fas fa-water"></i> 5.1. Ecuaci√≥n de Bernoulli para Gases</h3>
                
                <div class="formula-container">
                    <div class="formula-title">Ecuaci√≥n general de Bernoulli para fluidos compresibles</div>
                    <div class="formula">
                        $$\frac{P_1}{\rho g} + \frac{v_1^2}{2g} + z_1 = \frac{P_2}{\rho g} + \frac{v_2^2}{2g} + z_2 + h_f$$
                    </div>
                    <div class="formula-variables">
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">P‚ÇÅ, P‚ÇÇ</div>
                            <div>Presiones en puntos 1 y 2 (Pa)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">v‚ÇÅ, v‚ÇÇ</div>
                            <div>Velocidades en puntos 1 y 2 (m/s)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">z‚ÇÅ, z‚ÇÇ</div>
                            <div>Alturas geom√©tricas (m)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">œÅ</div>
                            <div>Densidad del gas (kg/m¬≥)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">g</div>
                            <div>Aceleraci√≥n gravedad (9.81 m/s¬≤)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">h_f</div>
                            <div>P√©rdidas de carga totales (m)</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                    <div class="alert-content">
                        <div class="alert-title">Simplificaci√≥n para instalaciones de gas</div>
                        <p>Para la mayor√≠a de c√°lculos pr√°cticos en instalaciones receptoras, se puede simplificar ignorando los t√©rminos de velocidad y altura, centr√°ndose en las p√©rdidas de carga.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="subsection">
                <h3 class="subsection-title"><i class="fas fa-fan"></i> 5.2. P√©rdidas de Carga en Tuber√≠as</h3>
                
                <div class="formula-container">
                    <div class="formula-title">Ecuaci√≥n de Darcy-Weisbach (general)</div>
                    <div class="formula">
                        $$h_f = f \times \frac{L}{D} \times \frac{v^2}{2g}$$
                    </div>
                    <div class="formula-variables">
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">h_f</div>
                            <div>P√©rdida de carga (m o Pa)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">f</div>
                            <div>Factor de fricci√≥n de Darcy</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">L</div>
                            <div>Longitud de tuber√≠a (m)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">D</div>
                            <div>Di√°metro interior (m)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">v</div>
                            <div>Velocidad del gas (m/s)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">g</div>
                            <div>Aceleraci√≥n gravedad (9.81 m/s¬≤)</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="formula-container">
                    <div class="formula-title">Factor de fricci√≥n para r√©gimen turbulento (Colebrook-White)</div>
                    <div class="formula">
                        $$\frac{1}{\sqrt{f}} = -2 \log\left(\frac{\epsilon/D}{3.7} + \frac{2.51}{Re\sqrt{f}}\right)$$
                    </div>
                    <div class="formula-variables">
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">f</div>
                            <div>Factor de fricci√≥n</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">Œµ</div>
                            <div>Rugosidad absoluta (mm)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">D</div>
                            <div>Di√°metro interior (mm)</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="variable">
                            <div class="variable-name">Re</div>
                            <div>N√∫mero de Reynolds</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="table-container">
                    <table class="data-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Material</th>
                                <th>Rugosidad Œµ (mm)</th>
                                <th>Factor f t√≠pico</th>
                                <th>Recomendaciones</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>Cobre</strong></td>
                                <td>0.0015</td>
                                <td>0.018 - 0.023</td>
                                <td>Muy liso, bajas p√©rdidas</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>Acero galvanizado</strong></td>
                                <td>0.15</td>
                                <td>0.025 - 0.035</td>
                                <td>Para exteriores, mayor protecci√≥n</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>Polietileno (PE)</strong></td>
                                <td>0.007</td>
                                <td>0.020 - 0.025</td>
                                <td>Muy liso, solo enterrado</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>Hierro fundido</strong></td>
                                <td>0.26</td>
                                <td>0.035 - 0.045</td>
                                <td>En desuso, alta rugosidad</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>Acero inoxidable</strong></td>
                                <td>0.002</td>
                                <td>0.019 - 0.024</td>
                                <td>Para interiores especiales</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="subsection">
                <h3 class="subsection-title"><i class="fas fa-wind"></i> 5.3. Velocidades M√°ximas Recomendadas</h3>
                
                <div class="info-cards">
                    <div class="info-card">
                        <h4 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-tachometer-alt"></i> Velocidades seg√∫n presi√≥n</h4>
                        <ul class="detailed-list">
                            <li><strong>Baja presi√≥n (BP):</strong> 2-5 m/s</li>
                            <li><strong>Media presi√≥n (MPA):</strong> 5-15 m/s</li>
                            <li><strong>Alta presi√≥n (AP):</strong> 15-25 m/s</li>
                            <li><strong>Conductos aire combusti√≥n:</strong> 2-4 m/s</li>
                            <li><strong>Chimeneas evacuaci√≥n:</strong> 3-6 m/s</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="info-card">
                        <h4 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> C√°lculo de velocidad</h4>
                        <div class="formula">
                            $$v = \frac{Q}{A} = \frac{Q \times 4}{\pi \times D^2}$$
                        </div>
                        <p>Donde:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><span class="value">v</span> = Velocidad (m/s)</li>
                            <li><span class="value">Q</span> = Caudal (m¬≥/s)</li>
                            <li><span class="value">A</span> = √Årea secci√≥n (m¬≤)</li>
                            <li><span class="value">D</span> = Di√°metro interior (m)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="example">
                    <div class="example-title"><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Ejemplo: Calcular velocidad en tuber√≠a</div>
                    <p>Tuber√≠a de cobre 22x1 (D=20mm) con caudal de 3 m¬≥/h:</p>
                    
                    <div class="formula-container">
                        <div class="formula">$$Q = 3\ m¬≥/h = \frac{3}{3600} = 0.000833\ m¬≥/s$$</div>
                        <div class="formula">$$D = 20\ mm = 0.020\ m$$</div>
                        <div class="formula">$$A = \frac{\pi \times D^2}{4} = \frac{\pi \times 0.020^2}{4} = 0.000314\ m¬≤$$</div>
                        <div class="formula">$$v = \frac{Q}{A} = \frac{0.000833}{0.000314} = 2.65\ m/s$$</div>
                    </div>
                    <p>Resultado: <span class="value">2.65 m/s</span> ‚Üí Aceptable para baja presi√≥n.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- COMBUSTI√ìN Y RENDIMIENTOS -->
        <section id="combustion" class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-fire"></i> 6. COMBUSTI√ìN Y RENDIMIENTOS</h2>
            
            <div class="subsection">
                <h3 class="subsection-title"><i class="fas fa-atom"></i> 6.1. Reacciones de Combusti√≥n Completa</h3>
                
                <div class="formula-container">
                    <div class="formula-title">Combusti√≥n completa del metano (principal componente del gas natural)</div>
                    <div class="formula">
                        $$CH_4 + 2O_2 \rightarrow CO_2 + 2H_2O + \text{calor}$$
                    </div>
                    <p>Relaci√≥n aire/combustible te√≥rica: <span class="value">10 m¬≥ aire / 1 m¬≥ metano</span></p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="table-container">
                    <table class="data-table">
                        <thead>
